### rolldown implementation:

rustpress build --input content/ --output dist/ --template blog

Internal steps:
Rust parses markdown → builds Vue Store JSON
Rust copies template files + assets to output
Rolldown/Vite bundles js/ and css/ (with the store data injected)
Final HTML gets proper <script type="module" src="assets/index-hash.js"> + hashed CSS

You could have a structure like:

templates/blog/
├── index.html          # base template
├── src/
│   ├── main.js
│   ├── App.vue         # (optional, if you go full SFC)
│   ├── components/
│   └── store.js
├── styles/
└── rolldown.config.js  # or vite.config.js

3. Key Features to SupportProduction vs Development mode (--minify flag)
Asset hashing
Support for importing CSS in JS (import './style.css')
Option to inline critical CSS
Ability to use Vue Single File Components (nice future upgrade)

